===== Division of the Solar Year

- *By Two (1):* Outgoing phase (Aries–Virgo, spring through summer) and Ingoing phase (Libra–Pisces, fall through winter). Modeled on the myth of Persephone.
- *By Two (2):* Solar half (Leo–Capricorn: Fire sign → Earth sign = dry path). Lunar half (Aquarius–Cancer: Air sign → Water sign = wet path). Processes with solid, condensed results: work in the dry half. Liquid results: wet half.
- *By Three:* Aries–Cancer (arising; Mercury). Leo–Scorpio (enduring; Sulphur). Sagittarius–Pisces (decaying; Salt).
- *By Four (Seasons):* Spring = Air (wet/warm, Aries–Gemini). Summer = Fire (warm/dry, Cancer–Virgo). Autumn = Earth (dry/cold, Libra–Sagittarius). Winter = Water (cold/wet, Capricorn–Pisces).
- *By Twelve (Zodiac):*

