===== The Stone Dragons — Spirits or Oils of Mineral Salts

- Key mineral salts: sea salt (NaCl), sal ammoniac (NH₄Cl), saltpeter (KNO₃), and vitriols (sulphates of copper, iron, aluminum, zinc).
- When heated: first water (phlegm) comes off, then an oily sharp liquid — the oil (spirit) of that salt. Oil of vitriol = dilute sulphuric acid; distilling sea salt or sal ammoniac → Spirit of Salt (HCl); saltpeter → Spirit of Nitre (HNO₃); mix → Aqua Fortis; add sea salt or sal ammoniac → Aqua Regia (dissolves gold).
- Mineral acids: only attempt distilling with adequate training and equipment. Perfect your technique on plants, wine, and water first.
- *Obtaining salts of a metal:* place metal or oxide of metal into the appropriate acid; spirit dissolves the metal; filter; crystallize; wash crystals. Each acid forms its own type of salt: acetic acid → acetates; HCl → chlorides; HNO₃ → nitrates; H₂SO₄ → sulphates; Aqua Regia → chlorides.

===== Work with Venus (Copper) — A Detailed Example

#lab[
  *Metal to mineral (opening copper):*
  1. Dissolve copper metal in diluted Oil of Vitriol (sulphuric acid) → deep blue copper sulphate solution. Or: start directly with natural bluestone (copper sulphate) — preferred.

  *Copper sulphate → copper carbonate (green verditer / man-made malachite):*
  2. Dissolve bluestone in heated distilled water to saturation. Prepare a separate solution of approximately equal amount of Salt of Tartar in the same volume of water.
  3. Add copper sulphate solution little by little to the tartar solution, stirring constantly. A green-blue precipitate forms immediately (copper carbonate = green verditer, the man-made form of malachite). Filter; wash until runoff is neutral (pH 7). Takes 4–6 washings. Longer waiting = darker verditer; temperature also influences color.

  *Copper carbonate → verdigris (copper acetate):*
  4. Slowly add distilled vinegar to the green-blue powder — it fizzes as acid reacts with carbonate (CO₂ released). Makes a deep green solution of verdigris. Crystallize → verdigris.
  - Alternative: suspend copper plates over warm distilled vinegar → verdigris forms directly.

  *Philosophical significance:* Moving copper from the realm of metals through the mineral realm and into the vegetable realm — "creating a channel through which the energies of copper may flow from the realm of metals into the vegetable realm, and in this way making it accessible to the animal realm." This transfigures, not merely transmutes, the metal.
]


==== Chapter 15: The Aurum Potabile

