#safety[
  - *Sal ammoniac sublimation:* Gas produced is very toxic — do not breathe vapors; adequate ventilation required; sublimation temperature = 520°C.
  - *Mineral acids (H₂SO₄, HCl, HNO₃, Aqua Regia):* Only attempt distilling with adequate training and proper equipment. Perfect technique on plants, wine, and water first.
  - *Antimony (stibnite, Kermes, etc.):* Toxic; can be absorbed through skin — wear gloves.
  - *Salt of Tartar attacks glass:* Always store in glazed ceramic containers.
  - *Never heat flammable liquids (alcohol) with an open flame.*
  - *Methanol (wood alcohol / denatured alcohol) is poisonous* — never use in any alchemical preparation. Discard all distillate below 76°C from wine-sourced spirits.
  - *Diluting acids:* always add acid to water, never water to acid.
  - Do not work when in a bad mood, unwell, or becoming fatigued.
  - All mineral and metal preparations: use only with supervision and consultation of a qualified medical doctor.
]
